body:
This has been reported to pyreadline as https://github.com/pyreadline/pyreadline/issues/65

@sergeyklay Looks like you depend on humanfriendly for your tests? There is an open issue for this there as well: https://github.com/xolox/python-humanfriendly/issues/44

To unblock my own tests I've been using the https://github.com/osrf/pyreadline fork. If you want a pre-built wheel there's one in https://github.com/domdfcoding/3.10-wheels

The original PR for reference: https://github.com/pytest-dev/pytest/pull/1281.

If this problem shows up again, I think we can add a guard for Windows 10 on `_readline_workaround`:

```python
    if sys.platform.startswith("win32") and sys.version_info[:2] < (3, 10):
        try:
            import readline  # noqa: F401
        except ImportError:
            pass
```

But I think we can close this for now and wait and see.
